title: Disposed date NONE? what does this mean
question: Filed:
question_tags: Divorce,Dissolution of marriage,Dividing debts in a divorce,Divorce and bankruptcy,Bankruptcy,Debt,Bankruptcy and debt,Divorce and family,Family law,Domestic relationships,Marriage
answers:
From your limited inquiry the best I can discern is that the case was filed, there’s been no resolution of the case and the case remains open. There are a number of items that must be completed to the court’s satisfaction before the court will grant the dissolution of marriage and make a final decision regarding assets, debts and children.
__________
Can't tell from the scant facts here. I suggest that you go the clerks office of the courthouse and ask them the status of the case.
You ought to consult with an attorney or perhaps with the Self Help Center to review your file and see what you need to do to complete your case.
